==Pronunciation ==
\Bla"tant\
==Adjective==
[[Cf.]]: [[bleat]].

Bellowing, as a calf; bawling; brawling; clamoring;
disagreeably clamorous; sounding loudly and harshly.

 ''Harsh and blatant tone.'' --[[w:R. H. Dana]].

 ''A monster, which the blatant [[beast]] men call''. --[[w:E. Spenser]].

 ''Glory, that blatant word, which [[haunt]]s some military minds like the [[bray]] of the [[trumpet]]''.--[[w:W. Irving]].